theorem
Th36: ((p > 1 & ( i mod p ) = 1) implies ( ( i |^ n ) mod p ) = 1)
proof
assume that
A1: p > 1
and
A2: ( i mod p ) = 1;
defpred P[ Nat ]
 means
( ( i |^ $1 ) mod p ) = 1;
A3: (for k holds (P[ k ] implies P[ ( k + 1 ) ]))
proof
